<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-3354] PDCIDFont.getAverageFontWidth always returns 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3354</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;PDCIDFont.getAverageFontWidth&lt;/b&gt; method is using the field &lt;b&gt;averageWidth&lt;/b&gt; as a cache, but fails to update its contents. Instead all the calculations go into a local variable with identical name,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;PDCIDFont.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; getAverageFontWidth()
    {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (averageWidth == 0)
        {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; totalWidths = 0.0f;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; characterCount = 0.0f;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (widths != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
            {
                characterCount = widths.size();
                Collection&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; widthsValues = widths.values();
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt; width : widthsValues)
                {
                    totalWidths += width;
                }
            }
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; averageWidth = totalWidths / characterCount;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (averageWidth &amp;lt;= 0 || &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt;.isNaN(averageWidth))
            {
                averageWidth = getDefaultWidth();
            }
        }
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; averageWidth;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A potential fix is the removal of the local variable declaration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;float&lt;/del&gt; averageWidth = totalWidths / characterCount;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
